The article provides background information on President Obama's meeting and event on regulatory reform. The President will meet with five Americans who have been negatively affected by outdated rules in the financial sector. These individuals represent the millions across the country who have been hurt by these regulations. The President will deliver remarks calling on Americans to support a new Consumer Financial Protection Agency (CFPA) and urging Congress to pass a regulatory reform package by the end of the year. The audience for the event will include members of Congress, state attorneys general, business leaders, regulators, representatives from consumer agencies, and community leaders. The article also provides brief bios of the five individuals the President will meet with, highlighting their personal experiences with financial issues and how the CFPA could have helped them. These include cases of fraudulent lending practices, misleading mortgage information, overdraft fees, and abusive payday loans.